      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Rinse the cashews",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add them to a strong blender. Pour in the hot water, nutritional yeast, mustard, garlic, turmeric, onion powder, and black salt.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Allow to soak for 20 minutes then process until completely smooth. Set your sauce aside until needed!",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cook bacon or pancetta until crisp",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Meanwhile, boil the spaghetti until al dente.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Drain and add to a large mixing bowl together with the Carbonara sauce, half of the cooked bacon and half of the parsley.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Give everything a good toss to coat and adjust seasonings.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "If you prefer your Carbonara with a little tang this is the time to hit it with a squeeze of lemon. I prefer it without but you are the boss of your kitchen.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Divide between bowls and serve sprinkled with the reserved bacon, parsley and freshly cracked black pepper.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Reserve a ladle of starchy cooking water before draining. Toss it through with the pasta and sauce in the pan over heat, the starch binds everything.",
              "cause": "Pasta drained too thoroughly, or sauce too thin.",
              "symptom": "Sauce won't cling to the pasta"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Cook a minute less than the packet says, drain, and finish in the sauce. Time it so the pasta meets the sauce in the pan, not the colander.",
              "cause": "Overcooked, or sat in water after draining.",
              "symptom": "Pasta is gummy"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Lower the heat first. Add the cheese a small handful at a time, stirring continuously, with a splash of pasta water to keep the sauce loose.",
              "cause": "Pan too hot, or cheese added all at once.",
              "symptom": "Cheese clumps when stirred in"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Give the sauce another ten to fifteen minutes at a low simmer. A pinch of sugar softens an acidic tomato base.",
              "cause": "Tomato or wine hasn't cooked down long enough.",
              "symptom": "Sauce tastes sharp or thin"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Vegetarian: drop the meat and add 200 g mushrooms (chestnut or porcini) sautéed until they squeak.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Lighter sauce: replace cream with crème fraîche stirred in off the heat, same richness, less weight.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The sauce reheats well the next day; cook the pasta fresh.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The dish sits in the Italian home-cooking tradition: a few good ingredients, a long unhurried cook, and a pan that has fed the family for years. Worth keeping its roots in mind when you taste, the silence between flavours is part of the design.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
